[Auction "S"]
1D X pass 1S pass 1NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 0, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "525ff1aa584e9d5f2391e6aca874c25f96a8415c11579c249fdbe92d9f34b222"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/overcalls"]
[Student "S"]
{WEST has 20 points, excellent \D stoppers and a balanced hand. 
She is two points too strong to overcall 1NT. Instead, she doubles.

EAST has an awful hand - but since he is forced to bid he says 1\S, assuming WEST wants 
to hear his best suit.

WEST now bids 1NT, showing the balanced 19-21 point hand. EAST passes, of course.}

